 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">If the mathematical model associated with the factorial plan is constructed with centered, reduced variables, the coefficients of the polynomial thus have very simple meanings: average 
  <span class="italic">a</span>
  <sub>0</sub>, main effects 
  <span class="italic">a</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="italic">i</span>
  </sub>, and interactions 
  <span class="italic">a</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="italic">ij</span>
  </sub> and 
  <span class="italic">a</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="italic">ijk</span>
  </sub> (Goupy, 
  <a rid="fsn3459-bib-0009" ref-type="ref" href="#fsn3459-bib-0009">2001</a>).
 </p>
